    "command": "openclaw cron add \\\n  --name \"Weekly Status Update\" \\\n  --cron \"0 14 * * 5\" \\\n  --tz \"UTC\" \\\n  --session main \\\n  --system-event \"\ud83d\udcca **Weekly Status Update Reminder**\n\nTime to capture the week and get your status out. Follow this flow:\n\n**1. Gather (5 min)**\n\u2022 Scan calendar for meetings, decisions, and outcomes\n\u2022 Check notes/task list for completed work\n\u2022 Pull any relevant metrics or data points\n\n**2. Draft (10 min)**\nUse this template:\n\n**\u2705 Wins & Deliverables**\n- [what you shipped, solved, or improved]\n- [team collaborations or customer impact]\n\n**\ud83d\udd04 In Progress**\n- [project name] \u2014 [% complete, expected finish]\n- [any pending deps or sign-offs]\n\n**\u26a0\ufe0f Blockers & Risks**\n- [what's stuck and what you need to unblock]\n- [concerns worth flagging]\n\n**\ud83c\udfaf Next Week Focus**\n- [top 3 priorities]\n- [meetings to prep for]\n\n**3. Polish (2 min)**\n\u2022 Keep it scannable \u2014 bullets > paragraphs\n\u2022 Add clear asks with owners and deadlines\n\u2022 Include shout-outs where earned\n\n**Action:** Send your status update before EOD. \ud83d\udcaa\" \\\n  --announce 2>&1"
